  "mayor_memo": "Mayor, the model recommends a paired program: rebuild and harden the I-695 harbor crossing to restore regional freight/emergency redundancy, while immediately funding bus-stop safety upgrades at the highest-ridership unsheltered stops. The bridge project protects port access and regional reliability but causes construction disruption; the transit project directly helps daily residents at modest scale, with curb and sidewalk tradeoffs. Safety benefits are strongest if both projects include lighting, refuge crossings, speed management, and bus-priority curb design."
